Use this directory for your final game and its module(s).  Only the
files in this directory will be marked.

Ensure you use the git add command to add your files to the git
repository.  For example,

git add module.c

Then use the git commit command to add the file contents

git commit -m "Added file" module.c

The use the git push command to copy the changes to the remote git server

git push

Constructing game:
First clone the latest copy from git, to the final folder under:

user/Documents/Ence260/embeddedSystems/ence260-ucfk4/assignment/final

From here reset your UCFK4 with the S2 button 
Then run make program command to make the program on the UCFK4

At this point you will be greeted with WELCOME TO LIGHT JUMP
point the board towards you with the yello led in the top right and the micro USB port pointed to the right.

When ready to start playing press the joystick in
your player should appear as a 3 LED high figure 
The controls are:

Pressing the joystick up to jump
Pressing the joystick down to duck

From here items will gradually flow at you along the cieling of the display or the floor and the object of the game is to doge as many of the items as possible

You have one life and will be greeted with "Game Over" if you unsuccesful avoid an item.

The amount of items dodged will then be desplayed and you can press the centre again to restart.

